      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "# /intake - Universal Content Intake\n\nUniversal intake system for URLs (GitHub repos, YouTube videos, articles, PDFs, etc). Routes all content to `~/lev/workshop` for analysis and processing.\n\n## Usage\n\n```\n/intake <url>\n/intake <url> --type=github|youtube|article|pdf\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n```bash\n/intake https://github.com/user/repo\n/intake https://youtube.com/watch?v=xyz\n/intake https://example.com/article\n/intake ./document.pdf\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\nThis command is a thin shim that delegates to the `lev-intake` skill. All logic, routing, and processing patterns are defined in the skill.\n\n```\nSkill(skill=\"lev-intake\", args={url: args})\n```\n\n## See Also\n\n- `~/.claude/skills/lev-intake/SKILL.md` - Full implementation\n- `/research` - Deep research using Sherlock Bytes\n- `lev find --scope=workshop` - Search intake artifacts\n\n\nARGUMENTS: https://github.com/rand/cc-polymath\n\n1- i want the agents in ~/.claude right away\n2- we can augment our skills-db / skills registry, check ~/lev/workshop/poc/skills after cloning\n\nno need need to do all the crazy lev scanning against fetures we should do it against the skills dir above"
        }
      ]
    },
